Jamaican Patois for a party, anything involving vibes fun or being over the top, also emphasizing objects of desire, or something good, that promises to be exciting. You can have bashment sessions, bashment clothes, shoes, houses, cars etc. Bash is a shorter form of the word Bashment with the same meaning, but to a greater extent. Bashy is another short form of the Bashment. eg. "Yeah the party was bashy iya, I'm soooo glad I went!". "No less than bashy/bash" meaning that the event, or item, is or was, quite bashy to say the least; used to express extreme joy or pleasure at something. eg. "That session was no less than bashy! I'm sooo glad I went."